summary: SummaryLancôme's Juicy Tubes Original Lip Gloss is the original juicy, high-shine lip gloss with four-hours of lasting hydration. Press. Shine. Repeat.
details: DetailsBenefitsEvery press of the tube tip applicator delivers ultra-glossy shine and the perfect amount of "sticky" texture you'll want to apply on repeatLeaves lips feeling lusciously juicy with 4-hours of lasting hydrationFeaturesFeel good texture, good mood flavorYummy scented flavors in three shiny finishes: sparkle, creamy & jellyKey IngredientsVitamin E hydrates & softens lipsItem 2562202How To UseHow To Line & ShineFor extra color and customization, use Juicy Tubes lip gloss with your favorite Le Lip Liner shade.Shade the outer corners of the lip as desired and apply a Juicy Tubes lip gloss on top.For a 90s-inspired look, Lancôme suggests using a nude, brown or neutral shade that is a shade or two darker than your natural lip color.IngredientsPolybutene, Pentaerythrityl Tetraisostearate, C18-36 Acid Triglyceride, Tridecyl Trimellitate, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Silica Dimethyl Silylate, Pentylene Glycol, Caprylyl Glycol, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Parfum / Fragrance. May Contain: Benzyl Alcohol, Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide, Sodium Saccharin, Tin Oxide, Anise Alcohol, Benzyl Benzoate, CI 15850 / Red 7, CI 15985 / Yellow 6 Lake, Aluminum Hydroxide, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, CI 45380 / Red 22 Lake, CI 45410 / Red 28 Lake, CI 75470 / Carmine, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, Alumina, Ethyl Menthane Carboxamide, Limonene, Mica, Polyvinyl Laurate, Silica, Tin Oxide, Linalool, Citral.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: How To Line & ShineFor extra color and customization, use Juicy Tubes lip gloss with your favorite Le Lip Liner shade.Shade the outer corners of the lip as desired and apply a Juicy Tubes lip gloss on top.For a 90s-inspired look, Lancôme suggests using a nude, brown or neutral shade that is a shade or two darker than your natural lip color.
ingredients: Parfum / Fragrance. May Contain: Benzyl Alcohol

reviews.headline: Long lasting
reviews.comments: I love the color and how it makes my lips look glassy. It is a stickier lip gloss but I don't mind it and it helps make the gloss stay on for a long time

reviews.headline: Pretty Gloss, But It Wasn't for Me
reviews.comments:
I love anything with sparkles and when I saw this gloss had them, I was sold!! I got the shade magic spell and while the scent was pleasant and the sparkly color looked stunning, I had to return it. The texture is on the thicker side, which I usually don't mind, but this felt like melted plastic on my lips. Plus within a couple of days, there was visible product separation in the tube. If you can get past these downsides, you'll probably like this gloss. 

ALSO, I recommend checking it out in person because the shades shown online don't really match the real colors.

reviews.headline: Love the clear!
reviews.comments: I bought the clear and a soft pink! I love both! They last a long time, and a little goes a long way! They're expensive for what they are, but they make the lips look fantastic for hours!

reviews.headline: Loving this stuff!
reviews.comments: I never tried this in the past, and it's expensive for what it is, but it does last! I think the smell and taste is more of an acquired liking, but it's grown on me! I really like the color after it's settled on the skin. I'll keep buying this!

reviews.headline: Absolute love it
reviews.comments: I wear the lavendar one all the time. It is very shiny and lasts long.

reviews.headline: Love the texture
reviews.comments: really sweet and smells good and looks just as cute on!

reviews.headline: Terrible
reviews.comments: I caught this on sale and bought it mainly because I was never able to afford them when they were popular and nostalgic. I ended up returning it. It felt gritty on my lips and gave me such a gross feeling.  The sparkles were also too much.

reviews.headline: Dreamsicle
reviews.comments: smells sooooo good!! light feeling, not sticky, and very pretty pale pink shade

reviews.headline: Lovely scent and new colors
reviews.comments: I never got the original one but fell in love with Magic Spell a couple years ago. I got a holiday sampler with Magic Spell, Marshmallow Electro and Tickled Pink. I didn't realize Juicy Tubes had scents until I bought the recent Cocoa Macchiato and Lavendar Latte. I was so pleasantly surprised at how much they smell like the real coffee drinks, especially the macchiato. Both so lovely and looks amazing and feels smooth and not gritty even with decent amount of fine sparkles. The lavender is lovely with blue and purple sparkle. Goes well alone or layered over other lipstick. The macchiato one is a beautiful sheer brown but pigmented enough to have color when worn alone. Love love love! Hope they come out with even more colors and scents!

reviews.headline: Would definitely buy more
reviews.comments: It has a pleasant smell as well as does not feel sticky

reviews.headline: Yuck
reviews.comments: Several years ago I was gifted the "Miracle" juicy tube which I really love! The texture is tacky without being too sticky if that makes any sense. I purchased the Clear gloss because I wanted a gloss without shimmer. What I received I would NOT recommend. Visually the tube/gloss is clear as it should be, but the consistency of the Clear gloss is slick and oily feeling. It has an absolutely terrible flavor... like rancid perfume. Can lip gloss spoil? Zero stars.

reviews.headline: Juicy Tubes Tickled Pink
reviews.comments: I love lip balm. I have every kind, Nars, Ole, Lanolips, Laneige.  This one is so far the thickest abd longest lasting. You can choose a sheer, or I liked a little more color w Tickled Pink. I wouldnt say its sticky but its very thick so stays on longer and leaves lips moisturized.  For color I'd also recommend OH Cocoa Creme.

reviews.headline: UGH!!! WHY? WHY? WHY?!
reviews.comments: does a cosmetics company re-release a loved lip product only to ruin it by adding a funky smell? I was fond of this back in its original release & had a few colors, but I can't wear this new one because of the nasty funky smell. Returning!

reviews.headline: I hate the scents
reviews.comments: I got the 2 new colors they just came out with. I HATE the way the smell! One is chocolate scented, the purple one smells like cologne and fall to me. I wont wear either! If the scent of a lip product isnt good to me i most the time wont wear it! I wish they would have kept the same scent.

reviews.headline: Best lip gloss on the market hands down
reviews.comments: I've been wanting one of these since middle school when I saw all the popular girls use them. Finally, as an adult, I was able to get one when they went on sale recently. I must say this is best lip gloss I've ever used. It feels and looks great on my lips and it's super long lasting. 10 out of 10!

reviews.headline: worst gloss EVER
reviews.comments: The new juicy tubes are horrible!! First off it was half separated in the tube as if it was actually 15 years old. I put it on just to try it, and the applicator has a sharp spot with scrapes and drags on the lips. Then, it turned to white goop in my inner corners. This is such a miss from lancome and very disappointing

reviews.headline: it's ok, just not the best
reviews.comments: I bought some recently.  When you apply even a small amount,  they tend to thread the moment you open and separate your lips.  You can visually see some trail of sticky gloss coming up as your separate your lips.  I kept magic spell because of the shade of color I liked.  The smell is good.

reviews.headline: I'm addicted
reviews.comments: This stays on great. It is a more substantial texture than most. Colors are good. I highly recommend it.

reviews.headline: Great Gloss
reviews.comments: I love Juicy Tubes!! I just got Lavender Latte and it's great! It is a sheer lavender color and tastes so good!!

reviews.headline: I would definitely purchase again!
reviews.comments: it's a beautiful gloss, i bought this for myself as a little treat I usually use drugstore glosses but decided for this one after I saw some ads. It's a thick gloss but in the best way possible, it leaves your lips very hydrated after using it and the colors are all pretty

faceoff_positive.comments: I've been using juicy tubes since they came out and I'm 53 now.  I get soooo many compliments on my lips. I sleep with this on as they are so moisturizing. Bring back TOFFEE POP and CARMEL GOSPEL please.  I still have a tube of each that I've saved for special occasions. The original formula is amazing.
faceoff_positive.headline: Thank Goodness they are back!!! Amazing

faceoff_negative.comments: I have 2 different shades that were included in the Xmas gift set. I have beeen using the "Tickled Pink" which is a great shade & has a watermelon taste! Yesterday, I decided to try the "Moulin Rose". BIG MISTAKE! Without thinking, I applied to my lips and was shocked with a bitter taste and a horrendous smell. It was as if I went to the perfume counter, drenched my finger with a rose perfume and then smeared it all over my lips. The scent was overwhelming, and I couldn't imagine going through the day with that stink right under my nose. I can't even imagine what it would do to any food or beverage I would try to consume. I scrubbed it off immediately! Seriously, I felt like I had sucked on a perfume bottle. Lancome, what were you thinking. Ladies, beware of this shade if you are sensitive to strong fragrances.
faceoff_negative.headline: Moulin Rose TOO FRAGRANCED
